JOHANNESBURG - As the country celebrates Reconciliation Day, it also marks the 58th birthday of the ANC's armed wing. The Umkhonto we Sizwe Military Veterans Association says young people do not understand the role liberation armies played in the struggle. READ: Solomon Mahlangu honoured 40 years since his hanging MK was founded on this day in 1961.
MKMVA president, Kebby Maphatsoe said, "Unfortunately since we took over power in 1994 we did not place the role in which MK played in liberation struggle. So our people do not know especially the ones who are born now you asked them about MK and they say, "what is MK?" "We blame ourself for not putting the history and the legacy of MK in the forefront."